<subSubSection id="B31DC7DEB4D5A3D395A5A45B92EFF6CD" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="654A7B14913213073CF8A2A61767ACDE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Supplementary description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9131DD0280A96D2C93F87B317FF458D" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B812A4585952CB34BED01EF9631CF09B" bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="AF49C8B7439E4627967A12F208F827F5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Tergite IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="60148BF4CABC9684420FC9B4819557EB" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8A, B, D</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized, with two nearly oval wax plates, separated from each other. Anal segment (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6FB7991CEC13528AB9B91718CF224AF9" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8C</figureCitation>
) rectangular, widening to apex, 1.1 times wider than long in dorsal view, anal style strap-like. Gonapophysis VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BD11DF53DFACC840F0DB023067CA9506" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8E</figureCitation>
) elongate, and slightly curved upwards. Gonapophysis IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A447734A3EFC2F3BF56B0B0C50391B32" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8F</figureCitation>
) with two middle teeth, distance ratio between distal middle tooth to apex and length of denticulate portion is 2.3. Gonoplac (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="207CABD6ACDEF067A8FE3530F64E9E84" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8G</figureCitation>
) rod-like, 3.8 times longer than wide in lateral view. Posterior vagina pattern as shown in Figure 
<figureCitation id="BBE37877C453B5E776E79A2A09C2E128" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Betacixius sparsus Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, female A genitalia, lateral view B genitalia, ventral view C anal segment, dorsal view D tergite IX, caudal view E gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, ventral view F gonapophysis IX, lateral view G gonoplac, inner lateral view H posterior vagina, ventral view I posterior vagina, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">8H, I</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8E371163D62CBB1F7254378AE4FCD37C" doi="10.3897/zookeys.956.50195.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439753" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
